## Renderer2D

The `Renderer2D` class manages 2D sprite rendering. All sprites must be added to a `Renderer2D` instance:

```typescript
const renderer2D = new Renderer2D();
scene.add(renderer2D);
renderer2D.add(sprite);
```

## Sprite2D

The `Sprite2D` class represents a 2D sprite. It requires a texture and supports optional properties like anchor point and size:

```typescript
const sprite = new Sprite2D({
  texture: myTexture,
  anchor: [0.5, 0.5],  // Center anchor
});
```

